comment.narrative: 2002-2004 average
The GVA data for 2012 are being computed by the National Institute of Statistics and preliminary data would be available byend-March 2013.
For 2009
Final data for 2012. The commitment of funds for 2013 started in October 2012.

title.narrative: Client days of training provided - Female (number)

comment.narrative: This indicator was included at the last project restructuring (September 2012) and after the training programs had been completed.
This indicator was not monitored during project implementation because it was included (as core indicator) at the last projectrestructuring.

title.narrative: Increase in CAP funding committed to beneficiaries under EAGF and EAFRD

comment.narrative: see sub-indicators below
see sub-indicators below

title.narrative: Functional network of Border Inspection Points to monitor food quality and movement of animals

comment.narrative: Finalized, target met; component implementation discontinued after first project restructuring.

title.narrative: GMO Laboratory at NRDIBH is fully functional. Construction of building for soil laboratory at RISSA is underway.

comment.narrative: GMO Laboratory equipped and accredited. The construction of a new building at RISSA was canceled and no new equipment was procuredas it was intended to be installed in a building for which the results of the seismic risk assessment were unsatisfactory. However,the equipment financed from the project and other sources was installed in the laboratory accredited as reference laboratory fornitrates and sludge testing. The target was met.

title.narrative: Functional training center able to train trainers, extension staff, food safety inspectors, agroprocessors and private sector, researchers

target.value: 30 trainers + 2160 extension staff + 400 food safety inspectors + 2050 agro-processors + 180 researchers

actual.value: 4 Training and Information Centers established, 35 trainers+2040 extension staff+468 food inspectors+5328 agro-processors+252researchers trained

comment.narrative: Target met and even exceeded in terms of staff trained.
Target met and exceeded.

title.narrative: Number of farmers receiving information / training regarding EU accession

actual.value: Comprehensive and updated information on CAP (Pillars I + II) provided to about 1.3 million farmers.

comment.narrative: Target met and exceeded.

title.narrative: Development of new technologies compatible with EU standards

comment.narrative: Target met and exceeded; All 41 sub-projects finalized.

The activities supporting the reform of the R&D in agriculture have been completed except the works for rehabilitation andmodernization of selected buildings, which need more time for completion. Works in advances stage of implementation.

40,800 man days of training provided to extension staff, 4,680 man days of training provided to food inspectors, 1,260 man days oftraining provided to researchers and 15,984 days of training provided to agro-processors

title.narrative: Technologies demonstrated in the project areas (number)

comment.narrative: 89 technologies were demonstrated under the project

title.narrative: Functional network of phytosanitary National Reference and Regional Laboratories

baseline.value: 2 NRL but in need of equipment and modernization, and 0 RL

comment.narrative: Finalized and target met; component implementation discontinued after first project restructuring.

title.narrative: Functional network of ANSVSA's National Reference Laboratories and Regional Laboratories

comment.narrative: Component implementation discontinued after first project restructuring.
Over 45% of funds allocated to NRDP (EUR 4.3 bln.) disbursed to beneficiaries.
